1
00:00:12,012 --> 00:00:13,721
EDUCATIONAL RIGHTS PROTECTION BUREAU

2
00:00:13,722 --> 00:00:15,806
ALL REPORTS
ARE KEPT CONFIDENTIAL AS A RULE

3
00:00:15,807 --> 00:00:18,684
PLEASE HELP OUR SCHOOL
THIS JUST ISN'T RIGHT

4
00:00:18,685 --> 00:00:20,394
THIS IS DAILY LIFE AT OUR SCHOOL

5
00:00:20,395 --> 00:00:21,729
IT'S REALLY MESSED UP

6
00:00:21,730 --> 00:00:22,939
PLEASE COME HELP, ERPB

7
00:00:26,151 --> 00:00:28,653
I FEEL SO BAD FOR OUR TEACHER

8
00:00:34,993 --> 00:00:36,953
EXPOSING THE STUDENT
WHO ASSAULTED A TEACHER

9
00:00:37,454 --> 00:00:39,330
REPORTING A SERIOUS ASSAULT ON A TEACHER

10
00:00:48,548 --> 00:00:50,966
<i>You will remember
the death of a female teacher</i>

11
00:00:50,967 --> 00:00:53,511
<i>that led to the establishment of the ERPB.</i>

12
00:00:54,012 --> 00:00:57,307
<i>The current Minister of Education
and head of the ERPB, Choi Gang-seok,</i>

13
00:00:58,725 --> 00:01:01,061
<i>is the victim's father.</i>

14
00:01:02,479 --> 00:01:05,106
<i>And Inspector Na Hwa-jin was her fiancé.</i>

15
00:01:07,984 --> 00:01:08,901
<i>Is it truly possible</i>

16
00:01:08,902 --> 00:01:13,156
<i>this has nothing to do with
the teacher killed by her student?</i>

17
00:01:13,865 --> 00:01:16,826
<i>These people are not working
for educational rights.</i>

18
00:01:17,535 --> 00:01:18,869
<i>It is cruel revenge</i>

19
00:01:18,870 --> 00:01:21,498
<i>for the death
of their daughter and fiancée.</i>

20
00:01:22,373 --> 00:01:24,000
<i>It is a personal vendetta.</i>

21
00:01:29,089 --> 00:01:30,006
Im Han-rim.

22
00:01:32,634 --> 00:01:33,593
What are you doing?

23
00:01:34,344 --> 00:01:35,761
Have you eaten, sir?

24
00:01:35,762 --> 00:01:36,679
Yeah.

25
00:01:37,847 --> 00:01:38,764
Let's go.

26
00:01:38,765 --> 00:01:40,600
Did you happen to see

27
00:01:41,601 --> 00:01:42,811
the press conference?

28
00:01:48,358 --> 00:01:49,400
Yeah.

29
00:01:53,404 --> 00:01:54,948
Is it all true?

30
00:01:55,657 --> 00:01:56,991
Yes, it's true.

31
00:02:04,332 --> 00:02:07,043
You'll be late to the meeting
if you just stand there.

32
00:02:07,544 --> 00:02:08,586
Come on, hurry.

33
00:02:13,174 --> 00:02:15,510
We have a lot to do.
Where the hell did everyone go?

34
00:02:20,765 --> 00:02:23,268
They're eccentric and...

35
00:02:23,977 --> 00:02:26,855
The members' eccentric,

36
00:02:27,564 --> 00:02:30,066
ignorant, and tyrannical...

37
00:02:30,775 --> 00:02:34,863
I do not see any potential for improvement

38
00:02:35,363 --> 00:02:37,656
in team members' capabilities--

39
00:02:37,657 --> 00:02:40,201
"Therefore, I am requesting
a transfer of assignment."

40
00:02:40,827 --> 00:02:42,786
Gosh, this is...

41
00:02:42,787 --> 00:02:44,789
ASSIGNMENT TRANSFER APPLICATION

42
00:02:48,168 --> 00:02:49,419
Deputy Bong Geun-dae.

43
00:02:50,211 --> 00:02:51,211
Yes, sir.

44
00:02:51,212 --> 00:02:53,173
What is this font?

45
00:02:54,007 --> 00:02:55,175
It's so eye-catching.

46
00:02:56,342 --> 00:02:57,176
Pardon?

47
00:02:57,177 --> 00:02:59,971
Let's use this font
for all official documents from now on.

48
00:03:05,518 --> 00:03:06,394
Oh, yes.

49
00:03:07,061 --> 00:03:08,563
By the way,

50
00:03:10,148 --> 00:03:11,858
that's not a good enough reason.

51
00:03:12,567 --> 00:03:15,903
If you want to be reassigned,
give me a convincing reason.

52
00:03:15,904 --> 00:03:19,240
A reason I can't logically argue against
in any way.

53
00:03:19,782 --> 00:03:23,036
Otherwise, it comes across as whining
to people like us.

54
00:03:25,747 --> 00:03:26,580
Hello, sir.

55
00:03:26,581 --> 00:03:28,957
We're so damn busy right now.
Get a move on!

56
00:03:28,958 --> 00:03:30,293
Look at the time!

57
00:03:35,632 --> 00:03:36,466
Safe...

58
00:03:45,558 --> 00:03:48,685
This report is about

59
00:03:48,686 --> 00:03:52,273
the assault of a teacher by a male student

60
00:03:52,857 --> 00:03:55,484
at Chukmyeong Foreign Language High.

61
00:03:55,485 --> 00:03:57,361
This is the teacher on the screen.

62
00:03:57,362 --> 00:04:01,698
The informant is a colleague
of the assaulted teacher.

63
00:04:01,699 --> 00:04:05,327
They also sent a video of the incident.

64
00:04:05,328 --> 00:04:07,121
- Play the video.
- Yes, sir.

65
00:04:10,208 --> 00:04:11,124
<i>Park Hyeon-ung!</i>

66
00:04:11,125 --> 00:04:12,834
<i>What the hell are you doing?</i>

67
00:04:12,835 --> 00:04:15,463
All that praise
has gone to your head, hasn't it?

68
00:04:19,509 --> 00:04:20,842
Mr. Cheon, are you okay?

69
00:04:20,843 --> 00:04:23,345
- Are you out of your mind?
- Hey, what's wrong?

70
00:04:23,346 --> 00:04:25,556
- What is it?
- Hyeon-ung, what's gotten into you?

71
00:04:26,057 --> 00:04:27,183
Stop it.

72
00:04:32,438 --> 00:04:35,357
TEACH YOU A LESSON

73
00:04:35,358 --> 00:04:38,318
CHUKMYEONG FOREIGN LANGUAGE HIGH SCHOOL

74
00:04:38,319 --> 00:04:40,488
Wow. Is this a school?

75
00:04:40,989 --> 00:04:43,491
What kind of high school looks like this?

76
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:45,034
I know, right?

77
00:04:45,660 --> 00:04:49,539
I heard they're the best of their kind.
They're very flashy.

78
00:04:50,415 --> 00:04:53,501
You guys go ahead.
I'll catch up with you shortly, all right?

79
00:04:55,003 --> 00:04:55,878
Let's go.

80
00:04:57,338 --> 00:05:00,007
<i>Grades alone don't guarantee
college entry anymore.</i>

81
00:05:00,008 --> 00:05:01,883
<i>- Especially Seoul National Uni.
- Yes.</i>

82
00:05:01,884 --> 00:05:04,803
<i>When I saw his student records,
he had public speaking...</i>

83
00:05:04,804 --> 00:05:07,222
Chukmyeong Foreign Language High School

84
00:05:07,223 --> 00:05:11,477
actually had a lower profile
than other foreign language high schools.

85
00:05:11,978 --> 00:05:14,647
But after that teacher, Mr. Cheon,
started working here,

86
00:05:15,231 --> 00:05:20,444
more students got into elite colleges,
and this became an elite high school.

87
00:05:20,445 --> 00:05:22,988
<i>- It's because they worked so hard.
- But you weren't...</i>

88
00:05:22,989 --> 00:05:24,906
Is that how he became famous?

89
00:05:24,907 --> 00:05:27,744
It was more because of his character.

90
00:05:28,244 --> 00:05:30,997
He's actually really famous
for being a true educator.

91
00:05:31,581 --> 00:05:32,665
A true educator?

92
00:05:34,375 --> 00:05:35,876
Why would a kid hit him?

93
00:05:35,877 --> 00:05:37,337
<i>You're amazing, seriously.</i>

94
00:05:38,046 --> 00:05:39,172
Gosh, sir.

95
00:05:39,672 --> 00:05:41,882
I'd always hoped to meet you one day.

96
00:05:41,883 --> 00:05:45,677
If I ever had the chance to do so,
I wanted to say thank you.

97
00:05:45,678 --> 00:05:46,596
Right.

98
00:05:48,014 --> 00:05:50,057
Allow me
to formally introduce myself, sir.

99
00:05:50,058 --> 00:05:54,227
My name is Na Hwa-jin.
I'm an inspector from the ERPB.

100
00:05:54,228 --> 00:05:55,187
Right, hello.

101
00:05:55,188 --> 00:05:57,856
I got into the Korea Military Academy

102
00:05:57,857 --> 00:06:00,275
after listening
to your EBS online lectures.

103
00:06:00,276 --> 00:06:03,570
That wouldn't be down to me.
You must have worked very hard for it.

104
00:06:03,571 --> 00:06:07,824
The things you said
now and then during your lectures...

105
00:06:07,825 --> 00:06:08,910
The...

106
00:06:09,786 --> 00:06:11,661
Gosh, this is just...

107
00:06:11,662 --> 00:06:12,997
- Are you all right?
- Wow.

108
00:06:13,539 --> 00:06:16,500
What's happening?
What's wrong with Inspector Na?

109
00:06:16,501 --> 00:06:18,002
What you said was really...

110
00:06:32,016 --> 00:06:33,393
Inspector, can't we just

111
00:06:34,227 --> 00:06:35,353
forget this happened?

112
00:06:36,187 --> 00:06:37,729
We have midterm exams soon.

113
00:06:37,730 --> 00:06:40,315
They're important
to Hyeon-ung and the other students.

114
00:06:40,316 --> 00:06:43,945
But still, he was in the wrong
and should be punished.

115
00:06:50,243 --> 00:06:51,743
Sir,

116
00:06:51,744 --> 00:06:54,622
could I perhaps ask a big favor?

117
00:06:55,790 --> 00:06:56,623
Yes, sure.

118
00:06:56,624 --> 00:06:59,668
You know your sign-off
at the end of your online lectures?

119
00:06:59,669 --> 00:07:02,003
Could you say it just one more time?

120
00:07:02,004 --> 00:07:03,756
"I believe in your potential."

121
00:07:04,340 --> 00:07:06,008
Oh my gosh.

122
00:07:06,676 --> 00:07:11,347
There just so happens to be a blackboard
and chalk right here, so...

123
00:07:11,848 --> 00:07:14,141
May I please ask you to do it?

124
00:07:14,142 --> 00:07:16,185
Gosh, Inspector.

125
00:07:20,565 --> 00:07:22,650
I believe in your potential.

126
00:07:42,211 --> 00:07:43,421
Wow!

127
00:07:44,046 --> 00:07:47,090
- You can't just touch it like that.
- What is all this?

128
00:07:47,091 --> 00:07:49,634
I bought it with my most recent paycheck.

129
00:07:49,635 --> 00:07:52,387
Believe it or not, it's dual monitors.

130
00:07:52,388 --> 00:07:54,389
It has a touchscreen,

131
00:07:54,390 --> 00:07:57,059
and the mounting bracket at the back
comes in handy.

132
00:07:57,560 --> 00:07:58,978
Right, it's a computer.

133
00:08:00,021 --> 00:08:03,356
It's not just any computer.
It's a portable monitor.

134
00:08:03,357 --> 00:08:05,692
The display is 16:9, and it's full HD.

135
00:08:05,693 --> 00:08:09,404
It's 15.6 inches, which is great
for watching Netflix and movies.

136
00:08:09,405 --> 00:08:12,617
And it's optimized for gaming
with the ideal aspect ratio and size.

137
00:08:14,243 --> 00:08:15,911
And see this small thing here?

138
00:08:15,912 --> 00:08:17,162
The white USB-C port.

139
00:08:17,163 --> 00:08:21,792
This single device can supply power
and support display output simultaneously.

140
00:08:23,169 --> 00:08:24,337
So it's expensive.

141
00:08:27,632 --> 00:08:28,466
Nice.

142
00:08:32,803 --> 00:08:36,599
PATIENCE

143
00:08:50,780 --> 00:08:52,782
Are you Park Hyeon-ung?

144
00:08:56,494 --> 00:08:59,538
You assaulted your teacher, Mr. Cheon,
a few days ago.

145
00:08:59,539 --> 00:09:00,790
What was the reason?

146
00:09:03,501 --> 00:09:05,545
If I tell you,
will you let me off the hook?

147
00:09:06,796 --> 00:09:08,047
No, you won't!

148
00:09:08,881 --> 00:09:11,550
Expel me or report me to the police
if you want.

149
00:09:11,551 --> 00:09:13,803
Don't pretend you want to know.

150
00:09:19,475 --> 00:09:21,309
If it's hard to decide,

151
00:09:21,310 --> 00:09:23,813
should I make it easy for you?

152
00:09:30,278 --> 00:09:33,072
Do not make me write
the Chinese character for "patience."

153
00:09:35,908 --> 00:09:40,662
The school still hasn't decided
how to punish that kid, Park Hyeon-ung.

154
00:09:40,663 --> 00:09:44,040
I thought the ERPB could really show them,

155
00:09:44,041 --> 00:09:45,835
so I reported the incident.

156
00:09:46,836 --> 00:09:50,756
Mr. Cheon is like a role model
to many other teachers.

157
00:09:51,882 --> 00:09:55,553
He makes you want to become more like him.

158
00:09:56,637 --> 00:10:01,016
Our school didn't attain elite status
simply because he teaches well.

159
00:10:01,017 --> 00:10:05,061
<i>Mr. Cheon is someone
who stays up all night with the students</i>

160
00:10:05,062 --> 00:10:08,690
<i>and gets more excited than they do
when they are accepted into college.</i>

161
00:10:08,691 --> 00:10:11,319
<i>Once the news spread,
students poured in to enroll.</i>

162
00:10:12,820 --> 00:10:14,904
To hit a teacher like him...

163
00:10:14,905 --> 00:10:17,950
I couldn't just stand by and do nothing.

164
00:10:19,869 --> 00:10:20,870
I see.

165
00:10:33,549 --> 00:10:34,508
Damn it!

166
00:10:39,180 --> 00:10:41,389
When do boys usually hit puberty?

167
00:10:41,390 --> 00:10:43,183
Generally, as hormones change,

168
00:10:43,184 --> 00:10:46,269
it spans from middle school
to the second year of high school.

169
00:10:46,270 --> 00:10:48,104
So he's probably at the end of it.

170
00:10:48,105 --> 00:10:49,814
He's all bravado and rage.

171
00:10:49,815 --> 00:10:53,777
He utterly refuses to listen,
and I bet his grades are utterly bad.

172
00:10:53,778 --> 00:10:56,279
Don't make hasty generalizations...

173
00:10:56,280 --> 00:10:59,200
I mean, I think you're mistaken.

174
00:10:59,867 --> 00:11:00,701
About what?

175
00:11:01,952 --> 00:11:02,787
Park Hyeon-ung.

176
00:11:04,789 --> 00:11:06,457
He's ranked first in his grade.

177
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:08,542
STUDENT REPORT CARD

178
00:11:10,336 --> 00:11:11,336
He really is.

179
00:11:11,337 --> 00:11:12,922
So why would he...

180
00:11:13,923 --> 00:11:15,216
He's ranked first.

181
00:11:15,716 --> 00:11:17,051
Why would he do it?

182
00:11:25,226 --> 00:11:27,061
EXAM MANAGEMENT OFFICE

183
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:31,482
ENGLISH DEPARTMENT, TERM 1, 2026
MIDTERM EXAM

184
00:11:40,408 --> 00:11:42,492
VIEWING IS PROHIBITED
TO UNAUTHORIZED PERSONNEL

185
00:11:42,493 --> 00:11:43,411
Oh, hello.

186
00:11:46,247 --> 00:11:47,415
Must be the exam papers.

187
00:11:49,291 --> 00:11:51,876
Yes, I'm the Head of Academic Affairs,

188
00:11:51,877 --> 00:11:53,629
so I have to check them.

189
00:11:55,548 --> 00:11:57,924
Wow, the exam papers are all here.

190
00:11:57,925 --> 00:12:00,552
When I didn't want to study for exams
back in the day,

191
00:12:00,553 --> 00:12:03,597
I used to daydream about stealing
exam papers with my friends.

192
00:12:04,724 --> 00:12:08,060
Coming up with ways to steal exam papers
was more fun than studying.

193
00:12:09,311 --> 00:12:10,521
I was like that too.

194
00:12:11,021 --> 00:12:12,148
Really?

195
00:12:12,648 --> 00:12:14,566
Mr. Cheon, it's an honor.

196
00:12:14,567 --> 00:12:17,026
Right, you can't be in here.
Let's head out.

197
00:12:17,027 --> 00:12:20,156
It's like we've led parallel lives.

198
00:12:21,282 --> 00:12:26,495
So why did Park Hyeon-ung assault you?

199
00:12:28,581 --> 00:12:29,414
I'm not sure.

200
00:12:29,415 --> 00:12:31,125
Do you have any idea at all?

201
00:12:34,128 --> 00:12:37,505
I created a special class not long ago.

202
00:12:37,506 --> 00:12:39,425
Right. A special class?

203
00:12:40,301 --> 00:12:44,972
<i>But I don't think the class
met Hyeon-ung's expectations.</i>

204
00:12:45,473 --> 00:12:49,225
That's right. This is ten
plus two over two plus... What is it?

205
00:12:49,226 --> 00:12:50,894
We learned this in our first year.

206
00:12:50,895 --> 00:12:52,520
We already covered that last time.

207
00:12:52,521 --> 00:12:55,482
The line segment A10 is seven,
and the triangle ABC...

208
00:12:55,483 --> 00:12:57,192
Why are we only doing reviews?

209
00:12:57,193 --> 00:12:59,110
How will this help us in the exam?

210
00:12:59,111 --> 00:13:00,946
We've been doing this for days.

211
00:13:01,781 --> 00:13:03,157
You should study with us.

212
00:13:06,786 --> 00:13:09,413
The class wasn't made just for Hyeon-ung.

213
00:13:09,914 --> 00:13:12,665
I had to take the other students' levels
into account too.

214
00:13:12,666 --> 00:13:16,587
But it was ultimately for his sake,
wasn't it?

215
00:13:17,713 --> 00:13:18,672
I'm not sure.

216
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:21,509
Isn't that just our perspective?

217
00:13:22,218 --> 00:13:23,928
DETAILED SCHOOL LIFE RECORD

218
00:13:25,137 --> 00:13:26,179
What about it?

219
00:13:26,180 --> 00:13:29,350
I just can't make any sense of it at all.

220
00:13:30,392 --> 00:13:32,436
You're a top student,
so why did you do it?

221
00:13:36,273 --> 00:13:40,151
A student as smart as you
must know what happens

222
00:13:40,152 --> 00:13:41,945
if you assault a teacher.

223
00:13:41,946 --> 00:13:44,824
What on earth made you angry enough
to ignore all this?

224
00:13:48,410 --> 00:13:52,455
These grades could earn you a scholarship
at one of the top three universities.

225
00:13:52,456 --> 00:13:55,834
You studied your butt off for 12 years
to get into college

226
00:13:55,835 --> 00:13:57,585
and even became the top student.

227
00:13:57,586 --> 00:14:00,214
So why are you acting
like you don't care about all that?

228
00:14:01,715 --> 00:14:04,844
I had bad grades, and even I find it odd.
Do your parents know?

229
00:14:15,187 --> 00:14:16,354
<i>To tell you the truth,</i>

230
00:14:16,355 --> 00:14:19,191
<i>I made a mistake
I shouldn't have as a teacher.</i>

231
00:14:19,692 --> 00:14:23,152
Once a year, the parents come to school
for college counseling,

232
00:14:23,153 --> 00:14:25,822
but Hyeon-ung's parents live far away
and couldn't come.

233
00:14:25,823 --> 00:14:27,240
So I paid them a visit.

234
00:14:27,241 --> 00:14:29,159
HYEON-UNG'S KOREAN BUFFET

235
00:14:30,411 --> 00:14:31,745
<i>They ran a restaurant,</i>

236
00:14:32,413 --> 00:14:36,750
<i>but they seemed so busy that I just ate,
pretending to be a customer.</i>

237
00:14:38,711 --> 00:14:39,545
What?

238
00:14:40,129 --> 00:14:41,589
I guess your parents don't know.

239
00:14:44,008 --> 00:14:46,719
Then I'll have to ask them.

240
00:14:48,095 --> 00:14:49,805
Damn it!

241
00:14:53,684 --> 00:14:56,729
Let go! Let go of me!

242
00:14:59,481 --> 00:15:00,482
Do you feel wronged?

243
00:15:01,567 --> 00:15:02,442
Angry?

244
00:15:02,443 --> 00:15:04,069
I said let go of me!

245
00:15:04,570 --> 00:15:05,528
Let go!

246
00:15:05,529 --> 00:15:07,531
Then ask for help.

247
00:15:08,866 --> 00:15:11,785
The first step in getting help
is to ask for it.

248
00:15:17,333 --> 00:15:21,128
Excuse me, Hyeon-ung.
This month's tuition hasn't been paid yet.

249
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:23,963
<i>Hey, son!</i>

250
00:15:23,964 --> 00:15:26,299
<i>Your</i> hagwon <i>tuition
hasn't been paid yet, has it?</i>

251
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:29,093
<i>The restaurant was really busy,
so I forgot.</i>

252
00:15:29,094 --> 00:15:32,680
<i>I'll pay it soon, so no worries.
Just focus on studying hard, son.</i>

253
00:15:32,681 --> 00:15:33,849
<i>You've got this!</i>

254
00:15:34,350 --> 00:15:38,604
<i>After Mr. Cheon visited, the restaurant
was ordered to suspend operations.</i>

255
00:15:39,104 --> 00:15:42,066
They said someone reported it
as an unauthorized building.

256
00:15:46,695 --> 00:15:48,906
Is that why you assaulted your teacher?

257
00:15:54,203 --> 00:15:55,955
Even in these circumstances,

258
00:15:57,790 --> 00:16:01,834
my parents went to a lot of trouble
and found me a private tutor.

259
00:16:01,835 --> 00:16:03,044
<i>Wow.</i>

260
00:16:03,045 --> 00:16:05,129
You did well in the exam.

261
00:16:05,130 --> 00:16:08,300
The exam questions were hard this time.
Do you have a private tutor?

262
00:16:09,343 --> 00:16:10,176
Yes, sir.

263
00:16:10,177 --> 00:16:12,261
Your tutor must be pretty good.

264
00:16:12,262 --> 00:16:13,597
What are they like?

265
00:16:14,390 --> 00:16:16,641
What? You're going to stop tutoring me?

266
00:16:16,642 --> 00:16:19,728
I'm going to stop tutoring
and focus on my graduate studies.

267
00:16:21,230 --> 00:16:25,526
My tutor suddenly quit
right after Mr. Cheon asked about him,

268
00:16:26,068 --> 00:16:27,444
which was odd.

269
00:16:35,703 --> 00:16:38,496
Sir, why are you picking up these stones?

270
00:16:38,497 --> 00:16:40,207
On their way to and from school,

271
00:16:40,874 --> 00:16:43,584
the kids either read books
or watch online lectures.

272
00:16:43,585 --> 00:16:45,504
I can't exactly tell them not to.

273
00:16:46,005 --> 00:16:49,341
I pick them up just in case
they trip on them and get hurt.

274
00:16:51,343 --> 00:16:52,177
Wow.

275
00:16:52,761 --> 00:16:57,348
No wonder people say you should be next
for Seoul Superintendent of Education.

276
00:16:57,349 --> 00:16:59,768
Please don't say things like that.

277
00:17:00,436 --> 00:17:04,439
Anyway, between Minister of Education
and Seoul Superintendent of Education,

278
00:17:04,440 --> 00:17:06,900
which is the higher position?

279
00:17:07,609 --> 00:17:08,443
Pardon?

280
00:17:08,444 --> 00:17:11,822
Well, our Minister of Education
is great in every way.

281
00:17:12,322 --> 00:17:14,616
On the other hand, he's not great at all.

282
00:17:15,909 --> 00:17:18,370
I was just thinking
I might change allegiances.

283
00:17:20,080 --> 00:17:21,915
- I'm being serious.
- My goodness.

284
00:17:23,751 --> 00:17:24,626
By the way,

285
00:17:25,252 --> 00:17:26,545
Inspector Na.

286
00:17:27,504 --> 00:17:29,006
What will happen to Hyeon-ung?

287
00:17:30,966 --> 00:17:32,760
We'll handle it as per protocol.

288
00:17:35,471 --> 00:17:37,264
When I think about Hyeon-ung,

289
00:17:37,806 --> 00:17:40,642
I feel it's right to punish him firmly
for what he did.

290
00:17:42,603 --> 00:17:43,895
But I'm not so sure.

291
00:17:43,896 --> 00:17:47,273
Please leave it to us at the ERPB,
future Superintendent of Education.

292
00:17:47,274 --> 00:17:49,317
Please don't say things like that.

293
00:17:49,318 --> 00:17:51,402
- Not at all.
- Please stop that.

294
00:17:51,403 --> 00:17:54,280
Superintendent of Education,
let me pick up the stones.

295
00:17:54,281 --> 00:17:56,824
- It's fine.
- I'll pick them up for you.

296
00:17:56,825 --> 00:17:59,202
Please give it to me,
Superintendent of Education.

297
00:17:59,203 --> 00:18:01,662
<i>Your Mimiminu channel
is popular with the students.</i>

298
00:18:01,663 --> 00:18:05,583
<i>So I thought my students might like
seeing me on your show.</i>

299
00:18:05,584 --> 00:18:06,667
<i>That's why I came on.</i>

300
00:18:06,668 --> 00:18:09,754
<i>As someone who is true
to their nickname of "true educator,"</i>

301
00:18:09,755 --> 00:18:12,965
<i>the care you have for your students is...</i>

302
00:18:12,966 --> 00:18:14,842
I've met with Hyeon-ung,

303
00:18:14,843 --> 00:18:17,470
and I think you should hear him out.

304
00:18:17,471 --> 00:18:18,888
The chalk snaps!

305
00:18:18,889 --> 00:18:21,140
TEACHER CHEON SANG-YEOL'S ICONIC FINISH!

306
00:18:21,141 --> 00:18:24,769
- I heard this in real life earlier.
<i>- I believe in your potential!</i>

307
00:18:24,770 --> 00:18:29,149
Back in my day,
everyone used to mimic this.

308
00:18:30,234 --> 00:18:33,152
<i>Even the bottom-scoring students
without any foundation...</i>

309
00:18:33,153 --> 00:18:34,988
Looks like you're here to meet a star.

310
00:18:35,697 --> 00:18:37,532
You don't seem like your usual self,

311
00:18:37,533 --> 00:18:40,410
with no interest
in getting to the bottom of this case.

312
00:18:41,411 --> 00:18:44,122
Mr. Cheon seems to matter more to you
than the cause.

313
00:18:44,123 --> 00:18:47,125
Or did the cause never matter to you
in the first place?

314
00:18:47,126 --> 00:18:50,087
<i>We didn't have college entry results
at this level before.</i>

315
00:18:50,963 --> 00:18:52,256
What's your point?

316
00:18:58,971 --> 00:19:00,597
Your perspective is already skewed.

317
00:19:02,683 --> 00:19:05,936
Aren't you thinking
that everything is the student's fault?

318
00:19:06,645 --> 00:19:09,856
Didn't you come here
having already decided who's at fault?

319
00:19:09,857 --> 00:19:12,151
Is what people are saying true?

320
00:19:15,237 --> 00:19:17,948
Are you really blinded
by your personal vendetta?

321
00:19:25,873 --> 00:19:27,082
If that concerns you,

322
00:19:28,333 --> 00:19:30,460
you may quit now.

323
00:19:38,051 --> 00:19:38,886
Hey, Im Han-rim.

324
00:19:40,762 --> 00:19:42,139
Let's do as we always have.

325
00:19:58,488 --> 00:20:00,032
Seriously!

326
00:20:05,245 --> 00:20:06,538
YEAR 3 STUDENT RANKINGS

327
00:20:09,124 --> 00:20:10,918
2ND - CHOI JI-HUN
TEACHER - MR. CHEON

328
00:20:12,252 --> 00:20:14,004
11TH - JUNG SU-JEONG
TEACHER - MR. CHEON

329
00:20:17,883 --> 00:20:20,469
NOAVIS INSTITUTE

330
00:20:22,429 --> 00:20:24,848
NOAVIS INSTITUTE

331
00:21:04,304 --> 00:21:05,305
Who are you?

332
00:21:06,181 --> 00:21:07,598
How did you get in here?

333
00:21:07,599 --> 00:21:11,394
I wanted to register at this institute.

334
00:21:11,395 --> 00:21:12,520
What school are you at?

335
00:21:12,521 --> 00:21:14,690
Chukmyeong Foreign Language High.

336
00:21:15,274 --> 00:21:17,150
I see. Chukmyeong High.

337
00:21:17,734 --> 00:21:18,860
Yes.

338
00:21:19,903 --> 00:21:21,822
Have you heard anything about our <i>hagwon</i>?

339
00:21:22,572 --> 00:21:24,408
That it's a good <i>hagwon</i>.

340
00:21:27,327 --> 00:21:28,369
Sorry.

341
00:21:28,370 --> 00:21:30,997
We're not taking any more students.
Registration is over.

342
00:21:30,998 --> 00:21:33,833
But I had a quick look around,

343
00:21:33,834 --> 00:21:37,461
and the classrooms were all empty, so...

344
00:21:37,462 --> 00:21:39,047
I said registration is over.

345
00:21:41,049 --> 00:21:41,925
Oh, okay.

346
00:21:42,634 --> 00:21:44,219
I'm sorry.

347
00:21:53,186 --> 00:21:54,730
- Excuse me.
- Yes?

348
00:21:55,731 --> 00:21:58,482
- You said you go to Chukmyeong High?
- Yes.

349
00:21:58,483 --> 00:21:59,442
Which class?

350
00:21:59,443 --> 00:22:01,444
Class four in the English Department.

351
00:22:01,445 --> 00:22:04,573
Then you must know Moon Hyeon-o well.
He's the class president.

352
00:22:05,157 --> 00:22:07,951
Yes. Hyeon-o. I know Moon Hyeon-o.

353
00:22:08,869 --> 00:22:10,454
Oh, that's right.

354
00:22:11,413 --> 00:22:14,082
The class four president isn't Hyeon-o.
It's Bo-hyeon.

355
00:22:16,001 --> 00:22:17,793
That's right. It's Bo-hyeon.

356
00:22:17,794 --> 00:22:20,171
I must have confused myself.

357
00:22:20,172 --> 00:22:22,673
- How did you hear about our <i>hagwon</i>?
- What?

358
00:22:22,674 --> 00:22:24,133
Are you even a student?

359
00:22:24,134 --> 00:22:25,551
Of course I am.

360
00:22:25,552 --> 00:22:26,719
- Who are you?
- What?

361
00:22:26,720 --> 00:22:28,930
- Who are you to come--
- Please stop.

362
00:22:29,473 --> 00:22:30,473
Bong Geun-dae.

363
00:22:30,474 --> 00:22:32,225
Hey, Hyeong-ju.

364
00:22:32,809 --> 00:22:35,269
Why did you transfer without telling me?
I was upset.

365
00:22:35,270 --> 00:22:36,479
Where did you move to?

366
00:22:36,480 --> 00:22:38,690
I moved
to Chukmyeong Foreign Language High.

367
00:22:39,566 --> 00:22:41,109
You got a haircut.

368
00:22:41,943 --> 00:22:43,069
How have you been?

369
00:22:43,070 --> 00:22:44,321
Good for you.

370
00:22:44,821 --> 00:22:47,741
I thought a foreign language high school
would suit you better.

371
00:22:48,450 --> 00:22:50,368
- How are things at school?
- It's the same.

372
00:22:50,369 --> 00:22:53,038
They still fight,
and there's still a pecking order.

373
00:22:53,872 --> 00:22:55,623
They don't bully me though.

374
00:22:55,624 --> 00:22:56,832
- Really?
- Yeah.

375
00:22:56,833 --> 00:22:57,751
That's a relief.

376
00:22:58,335 --> 00:23:01,171
How about you? Are you settling in well?

377
00:23:06,426 --> 00:23:07,551
Hey, pull over!

378
00:23:07,552 --> 00:23:09,763
It's Hyeong-ju.

379
00:23:11,264 --> 00:23:12,556
Hey, Kim Hyeong-ju!

380
00:23:12,557 --> 00:23:15,101
We have exams tomorrow.
Why aren't you studying?

381
00:23:15,102 --> 00:23:17,103
Wait, they're having <i>sundae</i>.

382
00:23:17,104 --> 00:23:18,772
- Damn.
- Hi.

383
00:23:19,272 --> 00:23:21,816
- Take your time eating.
- This is so damn good.

384
00:23:21,817 --> 00:23:24,318
Look at him stuff his face.
He's so damn big now.

385
00:23:24,319 --> 00:23:26,695
Studying for exams
made me gain so much weight.

386
00:23:26,696 --> 00:23:29,574
- It's not from studying, you idiot.
- I guess.

387
00:23:30,075 --> 00:23:31,575
Hey.

388
00:23:31,576 --> 00:23:33,744
Is the cheat sheet I told you about ready?

389
00:23:33,745 --> 00:23:35,079
Open up.

390
00:23:35,080 --> 00:23:36,789
You have to share it with me first.

391
00:23:36,790 --> 00:23:38,958
I told you we have different subjects.

392
00:23:38,959 --> 00:23:41,001
I said only the main subjects
are different.

393
00:23:41,002 --> 00:23:42,337
Eat this.

394
00:23:43,630 --> 00:23:44,922
Fuck. Seriously.

395
00:23:44,923 --> 00:23:46,466
Hey, whoa!

396
00:23:47,134 --> 00:23:49,009
Play rock, paper, scissors for it.

397
00:23:49,010 --> 00:23:50,553
Okay.

398
00:23:50,554 --> 00:23:52,221
- Rock, paper, scissors.
- Scissors.

399
00:23:52,222 --> 00:23:53,472
Rock, paper, scissors!

400
00:23:53,473 --> 00:23:54,724
You fucker.

401
00:23:56,143 --> 00:23:58,478
Okay, last one.

402
00:23:58,979 --> 00:24:00,147
Rock, paper, scissors.

403
00:24:00,647 --> 00:24:02,190
- I get it first.
- Hey.

404
00:24:24,504 --> 00:24:26,339
REPORT ON CHUKMYEONG HIGH

405
00:24:28,383 --> 00:24:30,260
BY BONG GEUN-DAE, ERPB

406
00:25:04,085 --> 00:25:05,212
Hey! Damn it.

407
00:25:05,921 --> 00:25:07,630
Hey, you fucking bitch!

408
00:25:07,631 --> 00:25:09,591
That crazy bitch.

409
00:25:10,383 --> 00:25:11,593
Where are you going?

410
00:25:13,345 --> 00:25:15,430
Fucking hell. Seriously, stop!

411
00:25:15,931 --> 00:25:17,223
- Stop right there!
- Fuck!

412
00:25:17,224 --> 00:25:18,808
Seriously. Damn it.

413
00:25:22,270 --> 00:25:23,437
Are you done running?

414
00:25:23,438 --> 00:25:25,315
Fucking hell, crazy bitch.

415
00:25:26,733 --> 00:25:28,944
- You fucking nutcase.
- Are you done running?

416
00:25:31,655 --> 00:25:33,531
That must hurt.

417
00:25:33,532 --> 00:25:34,823
It does, doesn't it?

418
00:25:34,824 --> 00:25:38,286
My heart almost exploded,
you fucking bitch.

419
00:25:40,413 --> 00:25:41,248
Han-rim.

420
00:25:41,873 --> 00:25:44,125
How many more beatings
until you get it together?

421
00:25:46,253 --> 00:25:47,295
Are you Joan of Arc?

422
00:25:47,796 --> 00:25:49,797
Why the hell would you butt in,

423
00:25:49,798 --> 00:25:53,051
trying to help an outcast
when you're just a loser yourself?

424
00:25:53,677 --> 00:25:56,096
You sure stick your nose in
when you ain't got shit.

425
00:25:56,846 --> 00:25:59,181
Rip her mouth open for me too.

426
00:25:59,182 --> 00:26:01,643
Should I? All right, Han-rim.

427
00:26:03,436 --> 00:26:05,981
Come here. I missed your lips.

428
00:26:06,481 --> 00:26:07,941
Hey, what are you guys doing?

429
00:26:18,034 --> 00:26:18,868
Just a grunt.

430
00:26:19,452 --> 00:26:21,829
Mind your own business and be on your way.

431
00:26:21,830 --> 00:26:23,081
Just be on your way

432
00:26:23,707 --> 00:26:25,542
and "salute" for your country.

433
00:26:26,793 --> 00:26:29,921
I'm a bit busy with my friends right now.

434
00:26:30,880 --> 00:26:31,756
Is that true?

435
00:26:33,341 --> 00:26:34,426
Yes, it is.

436
00:26:35,135 --> 00:26:36,136
"Friends."

437
00:26:37,304 --> 00:26:38,680
Whoa.

438
00:26:40,265 --> 00:26:41,599
- The weather...
- You scared?

439
00:26:41,600 --> 00:26:43,434
- The weather's weird.
- He got scared.

440
00:26:43,435 --> 00:26:45,352
Scared, my ass.

441
00:26:45,353 --> 00:26:46,979
- Are you scared?
- I'm not.

442
00:26:46,980 --> 00:26:48,522
You moron.

443
00:26:48,523 --> 00:26:49,691
Should I help you?

444
00:26:53,320 --> 00:26:54,904
Ask for my help.

445
00:26:57,157 --> 00:26:59,951
The first step in getting help
is to ask for it.

446
00:27:05,540 --> 00:27:07,667
Who is this man? Is he your boyfriend?

447
00:27:09,669 --> 00:27:11,254
Disgusting.

448
00:27:22,057 --> 00:27:23,892
That's so cool.

449
00:27:24,392 --> 00:27:26,519
- He's going.
- Hey, he's leaving.

450
00:27:36,112 --> 00:27:36,946
Please...

451
00:27:38,114 --> 00:27:39,991
Please help me. Please?

452
00:27:44,412 --> 00:27:45,413
I heard you.

453
00:27:55,965 --> 00:27:57,550
What are you going to do?

454
00:27:58,218 --> 00:28:00,720
What? Is a grunt going to hit a civilian?

455
00:28:02,180 --> 00:28:03,390
Yes, I am.

456
00:28:04,015 --> 00:28:05,141
Damn it.

457
00:28:09,896 --> 00:28:11,563
- Let's go, you crazy bitch!
- Damn it!

458
00:28:11,564 --> 00:28:13,315
- Fuck.
- Fuck, take me with you.

459
00:28:13,316 --> 00:28:14,400
Son of a bitch.

460
00:28:14,401 --> 00:28:16,069
Shit, this fucking hurts.

461
00:28:27,122 --> 00:28:28,123
Well done.

462
00:28:59,487 --> 00:29:00,572
- Thanks for this.
- Sure.

463
00:29:07,036 --> 00:29:08,872
All right, let's see.

464
00:29:09,956 --> 00:29:14,293
It's fascinating that the students
ranked 1 to 11 in the grade

465
00:29:14,294 --> 00:29:15,878
are all in your class.

466
00:29:15,879 --> 00:29:20,048
I'm sure you've already discovered
they all come from prominent families.

467
00:29:20,049 --> 00:29:23,927
The other teachers felt a lot of pressure,
so I took them on myself.

468
00:29:23,928 --> 00:29:26,472
- Just as I expected. I believe in you.
- Gosh.

469
00:29:26,473 --> 00:29:27,640
It was nothing.

470
00:29:28,433 --> 00:29:30,934
But they all seem to go to this <i>hagwon</i>.

471
00:29:30,935 --> 00:29:33,229
A <i>hagwon</i> called Noavis Institute.

472
00:29:33,813 --> 00:29:35,814
All the kids but Park Hyeon-ung.

473
00:29:35,815 --> 00:29:37,692
Are you familiar with this <i>hagwon</i>?

474
00:29:39,736 --> 00:29:43,782
I have heard a rumor that they offer
elite courses for a select few.

475
00:29:44,616 --> 00:29:47,910
The <i>hagwon</i> must be in a tight spot.

476
00:29:47,911 --> 00:29:49,703
They push their students so hard,

477
00:29:49,704 --> 00:29:53,625
yet the top student is Park Hyeon-ung,
who doesn't even go to a <i>hagwon</i>.

478
00:29:54,209 --> 00:29:55,834
I heard that <i>hagwons</i> these days

479
00:29:55,835 --> 00:30:00,089
are going all out to get the top students
for marketing purposes.

480
00:30:01,007 --> 00:30:02,425
I heard about that too.

481
00:30:04,469 --> 00:30:06,346
Okay, here's the thing.

482
00:30:07,889 --> 00:30:11,392
Let's say Hyeon-ung can't take the exam
because of the recent assault.

483
00:30:11,893 --> 00:30:14,312
Then who would benefit the most from this?

484
00:30:15,230 --> 00:30:17,314
Is it Noavis Institute
that's in a tight spot?

485
00:30:17,315 --> 00:30:19,818
Is it the kids
who would each move up one rank?

486
00:30:20,318 --> 00:30:21,361
Or...

487
00:30:22,320 --> 00:30:25,573
Is it Jung Su-jeong
who would move up not only in rank

488
00:30:26,199 --> 00:30:27,659
but also in tier?

489
00:30:31,621 --> 00:30:34,499
What are you trying to say right now?

490
00:30:40,255 --> 00:30:43,716
Mr. Cheon, do you know
a student called Han Ye-ri?

491
00:30:44,676 --> 00:30:45,509
I'm not sure.

492
00:30:45,510 --> 00:30:49,597
We were at Soyeon Girls' High School
before here.

493
00:30:50,098 --> 00:30:51,891
She goes there. Don't you know her?

494
00:30:55,144 --> 00:30:57,355
You were her middle school
homeroom teacher.

495
00:31:01,067 --> 00:31:02,609
Her name does ring a bell.

496
00:31:02,610 --> 00:31:03,652
Okay.

497
00:31:03,653 --> 00:31:05,946
Ye-ri did well academically

498
00:31:05,947 --> 00:31:09,534
and had been preparing to enroll here
at Chukmyeong Foreign Language High.

499
00:31:10,034 --> 00:31:13,287
But she never made it
because she missed her final exam.

500
00:31:13,288 --> 00:31:14,371
Is that so?

501
00:31:14,372 --> 00:31:15,581
Yes.

502
00:31:15,582 --> 00:31:19,001
And the student who was able
to come here in her place

503
00:31:19,002 --> 00:31:22,755
was Jung Su-jeong,
the student in your class.

504
00:31:23,256 --> 00:31:24,090
Isn't that right?

505
00:31:27,635 --> 00:31:29,804
Ye-ri had been doing so well in school,

506
00:31:30,346 --> 00:31:32,806
so why did she miss her exam?

507
00:31:32,807 --> 00:31:35,727
Was it because her parents
weren't as privileged as Su-jeong's?

508
00:31:39,898 --> 00:31:44,234
Is that why you created a class
that cut into her study time,

509
00:31:44,235 --> 00:31:46,028
stole her tutor, and pulled strings

510
00:31:46,029 --> 00:31:50,033
to sabotage her parents' store,
pushing her to violence, like Hyeon-ung?

511
00:31:50,950 --> 00:31:53,328
So she would mentally break down
and miss the exam?

512
00:32:03,212 --> 00:32:06,549
What? Do you still have
unfinished business with me?

513
00:32:07,050 --> 00:32:09,302
What do I need to do to end this?

514
00:32:09,802 --> 00:32:10,762
What?

515
00:32:14,432 --> 00:32:16,184
You just need to tell me one thing.

516
00:32:17,185 --> 00:32:18,353
Cheon Sang-yeol.

517
00:32:25,902 --> 00:32:28,446
What Cheon Sang-yeol did to you.

518
00:32:30,281 --> 00:32:31,449
Just tell me that.

519
00:32:43,086 --> 00:32:46,172
You think ranking first in your grade
makes you tier one, don't you?

520
00:32:46,839 --> 00:32:49,883
<i>Each person has a tier
that suits them best.</i>

521
00:32:49,884 --> 00:32:53,388
<i>In your case,
it would be around tier nine.</i>

522
00:32:54,263 --> 00:32:55,889
<i>Your parents are no different.</i>

523
00:32:55,890 --> 00:32:57,767
<i>In fact, your whole family is</i>

524
00:32:58,559 --> 00:32:59,560
tier nine.

525
00:33:04,148 --> 00:33:05,650
Son of a bitch.

526
00:33:06,567 --> 00:33:07,860
Son of a bitch.

527
00:33:20,081 --> 00:33:22,207
She caused a serious problem.

528
00:33:22,208 --> 00:33:24,502
Did you come all the way here
just on her word?

529
00:33:28,673 --> 00:33:32,927
I never said Han Ye-ri
was a problem student.

530
00:33:33,511 --> 00:33:36,180
You barely remembered her a moment ago.

531
00:33:37,098 --> 00:33:40,809
Yet you're well aware of the issues
she caused at Soyeon Girls' High School.

532
00:33:40,810 --> 00:33:43,730
The fact that the ERPB was there
means there was an issue.

533
00:33:44,772 --> 00:33:45,606
But...

534
00:33:48,109 --> 00:33:49,819
what are you playing at here?

535
00:33:50,653 --> 00:33:51,779
I think that's enough.

536
00:33:52,822 --> 00:33:54,323
You know Hyeon-ung...

537
00:33:55,783 --> 00:33:59,162
Park Hyeon-ung,
whom you are so concerned about...

538
00:34:01,873 --> 00:34:04,000
He will definitely take
the upcoming exams.

539
00:34:07,086 --> 00:34:08,463
Will he?

540
00:34:12,717 --> 00:34:13,843
Thank you.

541
00:34:17,889 --> 00:34:18,723
I believe

542
00:34:19,515 --> 00:34:21,267
in the potential of the ERPB.

543
00:34:39,702 --> 00:34:41,704
- Don't you think it's a bit much?
- Yeah.

544
00:34:42,955 --> 00:34:44,081
- It's Hyeon-ung.
- What?

545
00:34:44,082 --> 00:34:45,333
What is he doing here?

546
00:34:46,334 --> 00:34:47,210
What the hell?

547
00:34:50,546 --> 00:34:52,589
How could he even think about showing up?

548
00:34:52,590 --> 00:34:54,007
I know, right?

549
00:34:54,008 --> 00:34:56,260
Wow, so brazen.

550
00:34:56,761 --> 00:34:58,721
If it were me, I'd never come in.

551
00:35:20,827 --> 00:35:22,619
<i>What on earth are you doing?</i>

552
00:35:22,620 --> 00:35:25,373
How come Park Hyeon-ung
is able to take the exams?

553
00:35:25,873 --> 00:35:29,084
For messing up her mock exams,

554
00:35:29,085 --> 00:35:32,254
Su-jeong must now get tier-one marks
in all subjects in the midterms.

555
00:35:32,255 --> 00:35:34,340
I already told you this.

556
00:35:35,133 --> 00:35:36,133
Please have your tea.

557
00:35:36,134 --> 00:35:39,470
If this is how it is, I can't promise you
Superintendent of Education.

558
00:35:40,596 --> 00:35:44,099
Why can't Su-jeong get into tier one
when the others manage to?

559
00:35:44,100 --> 00:35:47,519
I pay you considerably more
than the others do. Is it not enough?

560
00:35:47,520 --> 00:35:48,896
For crying out loud!

561
00:35:49,605 --> 00:35:51,732
It's not my fault
your daughter is a brickhead.

562
00:35:52,316 --> 00:35:53,150
Excuse me?

563
00:35:53,151 --> 00:35:55,485
The others all do it,
so what is it with Su-jeong?

564
00:35:55,486 --> 00:35:58,406
Why set the table
if she can't handle a spoon?

565
00:35:59,157 --> 00:36:00,323
Why are you so brazen?

566
00:36:00,324 --> 00:36:03,994
The Superintendent of Education role?
I can get it without your help.

567
00:36:03,995 --> 00:36:06,621
It's you who has a lot to lose, not me.

568
00:36:06,622 --> 00:36:08,791
Can Su-jeong get into college without me?

569
00:36:10,459 --> 00:36:13,753
So just stay out of it, okay?

570
00:36:13,754 --> 00:36:15,548
I'll handle everything.

571
00:36:16,048 --> 00:36:18,134
And we're in a café. Mind your manners.

572
00:36:32,064 --> 00:36:33,441
Oh, you gave me a fright.

573
00:36:35,902 --> 00:36:37,819
- What are these?
- Hold them up.

574
00:36:37,820 --> 00:36:38,821
What?

575
00:36:42,450 --> 00:36:44,993
Didn't you get over it all
when you ran around the track?

576
00:36:44,994 --> 00:36:45,953
No, I didn't.

577
00:36:49,874 --> 00:36:52,919
It's now past six o'clock,
and I need to add RAM to my computer...

578
00:36:56,047 --> 00:36:57,923
What on earth is the matter with you?

579
00:36:57,924 --> 00:36:59,132
Damn it.

580
00:36:59,133 --> 00:37:00,968
It's Inspector Na Hwa-jin.

581
00:37:01,636 --> 00:37:05,222
- I don't think I recognize him anymore.
- What?

582
00:37:05,223 --> 00:37:08,017
He won't even try
to hear Park Hyeon-ung out!

583
00:37:08,517 --> 00:37:11,436
And he only sides with Mr. Cheon.
For God's sake.

584
00:37:11,437 --> 00:37:13,104
That personal vendetta thing...

585
00:37:13,105 --> 00:37:14,941
It's not like that at all.

586
00:37:16,901 --> 00:37:17,734
Then what is it?

587
00:37:17,735 --> 00:37:19,778
Ever since visiting Han Ye-ri,

588
00:37:19,779 --> 00:37:23,823
Inspector Na Hwa-jin
has been keeping an eye on Mr. Cheon.

589
00:37:23,824 --> 00:37:27,869
He told me to keep looking
into Mr. Cheon's students.

590
00:37:27,870 --> 00:37:32,041
That's why I looked into Noavis Institute
and paid them a visit.

591
00:37:32,541 --> 00:37:33,375
Really?

592
00:37:33,376 --> 00:37:34,502
Yes.

593
00:37:35,211 --> 00:37:37,463
Then why was I the only one
who didn't know?

594
00:37:38,381 --> 00:37:39,339
Why?

595
00:37:39,340 --> 00:37:40,466
Well...

596
00:37:41,217 --> 00:37:44,469
He said you're not very good
at deceiving other people

597
00:37:44,470 --> 00:37:48,015
and that you're a terrible liar.

598
00:37:49,725 --> 00:37:51,060
Damn it.

599
00:37:51,852 --> 00:37:52,687
Gosh.

600
00:37:53,604 --> 00:37:54,605
Whoa.

601
00:38:05,783 --> 00:38:06,617
Deputy Bong.

602
00:38:08,369 --> 00:38:09,704
What's gotten into her?

603
00:38:10,913 --> 00:38:14,750
She says she's acting like this
because she feels guilty.

604
00:38:18,212 --> 00:38:20,589
You call that fast?

605
00:38:37,898 --> 00:38:39,358
Why did you do it?

606
00:38:40,609 --> 00:38:43,362
Why did you pretend
you weren't suspicious of Mr. Cheon?

607
00:38:44,947 --> 00:38:46,991
I didn't pretend.

608
00:38:48,367 --> 00:38:49,744
I hoped otherwise.

609
00:38:52,663 --> 00:38:55,791
I hoped there would be
at least one teacher like that.

610
00:39:00,171 --> 00:39:01,672
I should've known better.

611
00:39:02,381 --> 00:39:04,841
Why didn't you say anything?

612
00:39:04,842 --> 00:39:07,135
I think you could've told me.
Me, of all people.

613
00:39:07,136 --> 00:39:09,430
No, I think you should've told me.

614
00:39:09,930 --> 00:39:12,475
I doubted your intention.

615
00:39:12,975 --> 00:39:15,811
You made me doubt you!

616
00:39:21,734 --> 00:39:22,568
Han-rim.

617
00:39:24,278 --> 00:39:25,112
Yes, sir!

618
00:39:25,696 --> 00:39:27,031
We aren't strangers.

619
00:39:30,910 --> 00:39:32,411
Let's do as we always have.

620
00:39:36,832 --> 00:39:37,666
All right?

621
00:39:39,668 --> 00:39:41,420
Understood, sir!

622
00:39:41,921 --> 00:39:44,715
- That bastard Cheon Sang-yeol did this.
- Damn it.

623
00:39:46,926 --> 00:39:49,887
He's not the type to sit around.
We'll have much more to do.

624
00:39:51,889 --> 00:39:54,266
Where are you going?
I said we'll have more to do.

625
00:39:55,393 --> 00:39:56,226
I was just...

626
00:39:56,227 --> 00:39:57,727
Come here. Just stay here.

627
00:39:57,728 --> 00:39:58,979
Mr. Na Hwa-jin?

628
00:40:04,026 --> 00:40:05,318
We're from the police.

629
00:40:05,319 --> 00:40:08,363
We received reports
that you harmed innocent students

630
00:40:08,364 --> 00:40:11,367
during your time as inspector
at Daehan High and Guun High.

631
00:40:15,663 --> 00:40:18,957
We are enforcing search and seizure
of the ERPB for abuse of power

632
00:40:18,958 --> 00:40:20,918
and violations of recruitment laws.

633
00:40:23,838 --> 00:40:27,257
<i>Following a large-scale search and seizure
of the ERPB,</i>

634
00:40:27,258 --> 00:40:29,551
<i>amid a personal revenge scandal,</i>

635
00:40:29,552 --> 00:40:34,055
<i>the prosecution is investigating
Minister Choi on charges of tax evasion.</i>

636
00:40:34,056 --> 00:40:36,349
<i>They said they would protect
educational rights,</i>

637
00:40:36,350 --> 00:40:39,436
<i>so I had no idea
they would attack our teachers like this.</i>

638
00:40:39,437 --> 00:40:41,938
<i>Especially not someone like Mr. Cheon.</i>

639
00:40:41,939 --> 00:40:45,775
<i>How do you see the ERPB's investigation
into teacher Cheon Sang-yeol?</i>

640
00:40:45,776 --> 00:40:48,403
It feels like the ERPB jumped the gun.

641
00:40:48,404 --> 00:40:50,071
After it was revealed

642
00:40:50,072 --> 00:40:53,116
that the ERPB was borne out
of a personal vendetta

643
00:40:53,117 --> 00:40:56,327
by the victim's father and fiancé
over a two-year-old case,

644
00:40:56,328 --> 00:40:58,288
<i>it seems they tried to muddy the waters</i>

645
00:40:58,289 --> 00:41:01,124
<i>by shifting their targets
from students to teachers.</i>

646
00:41:01,125 --> 00:41:04,794
<i>They likely targeted a well-known figure
like Cheon Sang-yeol</i>

647
00:41:04,795 --> 00:41:06,422
<i>for similar reasons.</i>

648
00:41:08,466 --> 00:41:11,593
It looks like Choi Gang-seok
has screwed up big time.

649
00:41:11,594 --> 00:41:13,262
Should we run some articles?

650
00:41:14,305 --> 00:41:18,224
How about we corner the ERPB
and push to impeach the president?

651
00:41:18,225 --> 00:41:22,354
"We were duped by Minister Choi
when he first proposed the ERPB bill."

652
00:41:24,607 --> 00:41:26,567
Perfect time to shift the blame, isn't it?

653
00:41:36,368 --> 00:41:38,621
Announce we'll hold
a Board of Education meeting.

654
00:41:40,414 --> 00:41:41,956
In the hiring of the inspector,

655
00:41:41,957 --> 00:41:44,793
there was abuse of power
by the Minister of Education.

656
00:41:45,294 --> 00:41:46,712
Do you admit it?

657
00:41:57,765 --> 00:42:00,558
It all played out exactly as you expected.

658
00:42:00,559 --> 00:42:02,519
Impressive connections, don't you think?

659
00:42:02,520 --> 00:42:05,230
The fact that the prosecution,
the police, the press,

660
00:42:05,231 --> 00:42:07,815
and even the tax office
all operated as one is just...

661
00:42:07,816 --> 00:42:10,151
I bet even the president can't match that.

662
00:42:10,152 --> 00:42:12,529
Is this the time to be impressed?

663
00:42:12,530 --> 00:42:13,948
Shouldn't we do something?

664
00:42:14,865 --> 00:42:17,534
We have to stay locked up here
until next week anyway.

665
00:42:17,535 --> 00:42:18,827
Next week? Why?

666
00:42:21,163 --> 00:42:23,666
Chukmyeong High's exams are next week.

667
00:42:24,416 --> 00:42:26,918
They won't let us do anything before then.

668
00:42:26,919 --> 00:42:28,254
Goddamn it.

669
00:42:28,796 --> 00:42:30,797
S sub n equals n squared times a sub n.

670
00:42:30,798 --> 00:42:33,259
Something should come to mind
when you see this.

671
00:42:38,013 --> 00:42:40,265
Right, focus on me.

672
00:42:40,266 --> 00:42:44,436
Okay, here it's n plus one squared
times a sub n plus one...

673
00:42:44,937 --> 00:42:45,853
You're here.

674
00:42:45,854 --> 00:42:47,106
Please take a seat.

675
00:42:53,362 --> 00:42:55,863
I saw you took care of the ERPB
all on your own.

676
00:42:55,864 --> 00:42:57,408
All I have are my connections.

677
00:42:58,325 --> 00:43:01,328
- You were a great help too.
- It was nothing.

678
00:43:02,329 --> 00:43:04,373
Enough about the ERPB.

679
00:43:05,332 --> 00:43:06,458
What about Su-jeong?

680
00:43:09,128 --> 00:43:11,005
Right, ma'am.

681
00:43:24,351 --> 00:43:25,727
What is this?

682
00:43:25,728 --> 00:43:27,729
Tell Su-jeong to memorize it all.

683
00:43:27,730 --> 00:43:30,733
Since she can't handle a spoon,
we should spoon-feed her.

684
00:43:32,401 --> 00:43:34,236
You didn't show the other kids, right?

685
00:43:36,030 --> 00:43:39,365
Please take care of my fundraiser
for the Superintendent of Education.

686
00:43:39,366 --> 00:43:40,909
Don't worry.

687
00:43:41,410 --> 00:43:45,080
We will donate enough
to have your funding overflowing.

688
00:43:45,706 --> 00:43:48,751
If this exam goes well,
you'll be the Superintendent of Education.

689
00:43:49,793 --> 00:43:50,794
My gosh.

690
00:43:54,590 --> 00:43:56,674
When I'm told to provide backup support,

691
00:43:56,675 --> 00:44:02,555
I send necessary materials
to the inspectors and look things up...

692
00:44:02,556 --> 00:44:04,808
You won't get anything
from questioning him.

693
00:44:06,018 --> 00:44:09,188
He's just a public official
who does what his superiors tell him.

694
00:44:11,398 --> 00:44:13,275
Don't waste your energy and let him go.

695
00:44:16,820 --> 00:44:18,864
- Deputy Bong.
- Hey.

696
00:44:19,865 --> 00:44:22,660
They said I'm free to go now.

697
00:44:23,577 --> 00:44:24,870
Bring that thing to me.

698
00:44:27,206 --> 00:44:28,623
Pardon? Bring what...

699
00:44:28,624 --> 00:44:30,709
The assignment transfer application.

700
00:44:31,293 --> 00:44:33,420
I'll sign it off for you,
so bring it to me.

701
00:44:34,004 --> 00:44:34,880
You wanted it.

702
00:44:35,881 --> 00:44:39,842
I thought about it again,
and I've changed my mind a little.

703
00:44:39,843 --> 00:44:41,177
Just bring it, you brat.

704
00:44:41,178 --> 00:44:43,054
But I really thought about it again--

705
00:44:43,055 --> 00:44:44,473
Just bring it to me!

706
00:44:51,063 --> 00:44:51,897
Yes, sir.

707
00:44:53,440 --> 00:44:55,149
- Assignment transfer?
- No, but...

708
00:44:55,150 --> 00:44:56,484
- I really--
- Hurry up!

709
00:44:56,485 --> 00:44:58,445
Yes, sir. I'll go and get it.

710
00:45:00,614 --> 00:45:01,990
I AM REQUESTING A TRANSFER OF...

711
00:45:06,120 --> 00:45:08,080
Please just take a look.

712
00:45:08,914 --> 00:45:09,748
Wait...

713
00:45:18,257 --> 00:45:21,926
The way things are now,
staying at the ERPB won't do you any good.

714
00:45:21,927 --> 00:45:23,470
Inspector Na Hwa-jin,

715
00:45:24,179 --> 00:45:25,264
you sign it too.

716
00:45:28,434 --> 00:45:31,437
I won't think of it as you whining,
so stand tall.

717
00:45:32,855 --> 00:45:33,897
Keep your chin up.

718
00:45:49,496 --> 00:45:50,706
Goodbye.

719
00:46:01,091 --> 00:46:03,010
Oops, sorry.

720
00:46:06,013 --> 00:46:07,598
What? Get back to studying.

721
00:46:08,182 --> 00:46:09,767
Quick, pick it up. It's in the way.

722
00:46:12,144 --> 00:46:13,812
You'll make him cry.

723
00:46:20,611 --> 00:46:22,112
Good morning.

724
00:46:23,947 --> 00:46:26,283
Put your textbooks away,
and shut the other door.

725
00:46:41,048 --> 00:46:42,341
Good luck on the exam.

726
00:47:14,873 --> 00:47:15,957
Take care, sir.

727
00:47:15,958 --> 00:47:17,917
- Goodbye, sir.
- You did well.

728
00:47:17,918 --> 00:47:21,255
<i>What was your real motive
for establishing the ERPB?</i>

729
00:47:22,840 --> 00:47:24,508
Do you seek to avenge your daughter?

730
00:47:25,717 --> 00:47:28,761
Or are you trying
to use your dead daughter

731
00:47:28,762 --> 00:47:30,013
for political gain?

732
00:47:30,848 --> 00:47:33,683
Why did you target the teacher
Cheon Sang-yeol?

733
00:47:33,684 --> 00:47:36,435
As the public turned against you
over revenge allegations,

734
00:47:36,436 --> 00:47:37,646
weren't you deflecting?

735
00:47:42,860 --> 00:47:44,903
EXAM MANAGEMENT OFFICE
RESTRICTED AREA

736
00:47:49,783 --> 00:47:51,701
EXAM MARKING PROGRAM
SELECT TOPIC: CALCULUS

737
00:47:51,702 --> 00:47:53,245
Can you pass that to me?

738
00:47:57,457 --> 00:47:59,292
JUNG SU-JEONG
SUBJECT: CALCULUS

739
00:47:59,293 --> 00:48:00,419
It's correct.

740
00:48:05,299 --> 00:48:06,758
JUNG SU-JEONG, SCORE: 0

741
00:48:09,636 --> 00:48:11,889
Pass me the math exam paper.

742
00:48:13,140 --> 00:48:13,974
Here.

743
00:48:17,895 --> 00:48:19,730
- Pass me the English exam paper.
- Here.

744
00:48:23,400 --> 00:48:25,277
What? What's going on?

745
00:48:35,829 --> 00:48:37,038
Stop the exam immediately.

746
00:48:37,039 --> 00:48:39,081
- What do you mean?
- Stop right now.

747
00:48:39,082 --> 00:48:42,419
Those at the back! Collect all exam papers
and answer sheets. Now!

748
00:48:43,003 --> 00:48:44,879
- The exam isn't over yet, sir.
- This is...

749
00:48:44,880 --> 00:48:47,507
What are you waiting for? Do it now!

750
00:48:48,091 --> 00:48:49,300
The exam paper is...

751
00:48:49,301 --> 00:48:50,636
Wait!

752
00:48:53,388 --> 00:48:54,222
What?

753
00:48:55,390 --> 00:48:56,682
The exam isn't over yet.

754
00:48:56,683 --> 00:48:57,935
Damn it.

755
00:48:58,477 --> 00:49:01,063
- Collect them right now!
- Stop right there.

756
00:49:01,730 --> 00:49:03,899
Guys, sit down.
You have to take your exam.

757
00:49:05,817 --> 00:49:07,944
That's right. Good.

758
00:49:07,945 --> 00:49:10,529
You were so worried
the kids might get distracted.

759
00:49:10,530 --> 00:49:13,617
Is there a particular reason
they shouldn't take their exams?

760
00:49:15,661 --> 00:49:17,036
They're the wrong exam papers.

761
00:49:17,037 --> 00:49:19,956
We'll find out what happened,
void all exams, and retake them.

762
00:49:19,957 --> 00:49:21,582
No. There will be no retakes.

763
00:49:21,583 --> 00:49:23,251
Someone switched the exam...

764
00:49:28,465 --> 00:49:30,717
The ERPB replaced the exam papers.

765
00:49:31,593 --> 00:49:32,427
How...

766
00:49:32,928 --> 00:49:34,845
- How did the ERPB...
- I know, right?

767
00:49:34,846 --> 00:49:39,142
We were all locked up at
the police station, so how did we do it?

768
00:49:40,060 --> 00:49:41,395
Inspector Na Hwa-jin,

769
00:49:42,145 --> 00:49:43,271
you sign it too.

770
00:49:49,027 --> 00:49:51,488
MINISTER OF EDUCATION
REPLACE THE EXAM PAPERS

771
00:49:55,617 --> 00:49:57,284
TEAM LEADER

772
00:49:57,285 --> 00:49:59,246
CHEON SANG-YEOL SON OF A BITCH

773
00:50:04,376 --> 00:50:05,543
CHUKMYEONG HIGH GUIDE.PDF

774
00:50:05,544 --> 00:50:08,171
PS I'M STEALING THEM.
MY HIGH SCHOOL DREAMS HAVE COME TRUE

775
00:50:37,909 --> 00:50:40,537
It's clear you tampered with the exam,
so it stops now.

776
00:50:41,121 --> 00:50:43,247
Give that here. Stop it. Stop working.

777
00:50:43,248 --> 00:50:45,166
Stop working, you punk!

778
00:50:45,167 --> 00:50:46,126
Let go!

779
00:50:47,210 --> 00:50:48,128
Let go!

780
00:50:49,337 --> 00:50:50,505
Let go, you jerk!

781
00:50:54,092 --> 00:50:55,010
Mr. Cheon!

782
00:50:56,303 --> 00:50:59,305
You must not cause a disturbance
or be disruptive during exams,

783
00:50:59,306 --> 00:51:00,807
even if you are a teacher.

784
00:51:02,267 --> 00:51:03,101
Damn it.

785
00:51:07,022 --> 00:51:08,148
Damn you, ERPB!

786
00:51:10,150 --> 00:51:11,067
Mr. Cheon!

787
00:51:11,068 --> 00:51:13,236
You damn bastard!

788
00:51:26,124 --> 00:51:28,501
ERPB SPECIAL PROJECT

789
00:51:28,502 --> 00:51:31,463
Mic test. One, two.

790
00:51:32,005 --> 00:51:35,007
Hello, this is
the Educational Rights Protection Bureau.

791
00:51:35,008 --> 00:51:39,553
Please stop your exam for a moment
and look at the screen.

792
00:51:39,554 --> 00:51:43,265
A special video will start shortly.

793
00:51:43,266 --> 00:51:44,434
Title.

794
00:51:45,310 --> 00:51:48,771
<i>The Reason the ERPB
Replaced the Exam Papers.</i>

795
00:51:48,772 --> 00:51:51,775
The reason.

796
00:51:54,778 --> 00:51:58,364
THE REASON THE ERPB
REPLACED THE EXAM PAPERS

797
00:51:58,365 --> 00:52:00,741
On Mr. Cheon's original exam paper,

798
00:52:00,742 --> 00:52:04,161
the answer to question one
was "one over two."

799
00:52:04,162 --> 00:52:06,497
Being multiple choice,
the answer was number one.

800
00:52:06,498 --> 00:52:08,125
What about Jung Su-jeong?

801
00:52:09,417 --> 00:52:11,419
<i>Jung Su-jeong's answer to question one is...</i>

802
00:52:16,007 --> 00:52:16,842
number one too.

803
00:52:17,425 --> 00:52:20,052
And the answer
to written-response question one

804
00:52:20,053 --> 00:52:21,554
was "three cosine theta

805
00:52:21,555 --> 00:52:25,432
equals four cosine cubed theta
minus three cosine theta."

806
00:52:25,433 --> 00:52:27,227
What about Jung Su-jeong?

807
00:52:28,895 --> 00:52:31,064
<i>Jung Su-jeong's answer is...</i>

808
00:52:36,236 --> 00:52:37,653
also "cosine three theta

809
00:52:37,654 --> 00:52:42,741
equals four cosine cubed theta
minus three cosine theta."

810
00:52:42,742 --> 00:52:47,454
Today, Jung Su-jeong took the exam
with the exam papers replaced by the ERPB.

811
00:52:47,455 --> 00:52:48,665
Her math score is

812
00:52:49,249 --> 00:52:50,333
zero.

813
00:52:52,127 --> 00:52:53,419
But the thing is...

814
00:52:53,420 --> 00:52:59,341
<i>If you compare the math exam paper
Mr. Cheon had originally set</i>

815
00:52:59,342 --> 00:53:03,180
with Jung Su-jeong's answer card,

816
00:53:03,930 --> 00:53:05,182
the score would be 100.

817
00:53:05,807 --> 00:53:08,934
The exam questions were actually the same.

818
00:53:08,935 --> 00:53:12,856
Only the order of the questions
had changed.

819
00:53:13,356 --> 00:53:17,736
A top student who has always ranked 11th
in her year got a zero.

820
00:53:18,236 --> 00:53:20,654
She may not have felt well today,

821
00:53:20,655 --> 00:53:23,490
or she may have misaligned her answers
by one row.

822
00:53:23,491 --> 00:53:26,536
Even so, it's too much of a coincidence

823
00:53:27,120 --> 00:53:31,457
that all her answers match
the order of the questions

824
00:53:31,458 --> 00:53:34,127
on the exam paper
Mr. Cheon had originally set.

825
00:53:35,253 --> 00:53:36,254
That's right.

826
00:53:49,851 --> 00:53:52,812
Destroying evidence
is a serious criminal offense!

827
00:53:53,647 --> 00:53:55,732
- Were the answers on her hands?
- Is she crazy?

828
00:53:57,234 --> 00:53:58,068
<i>What is this?</i>

829
00:53:58,652 --> 00:54:00,778
<i>Tell Su-jeong to memorize it all.</i>

830
00:54:00,779 --> 00:54:03,782
<i>Since she can't handle a spoon,
we should spoon-feed her.</i>

831
00:54:05,242 --> 00:54:06,076
<i>You didn't show...</i>

832
00:54:07,702 --> 00:54:08,995
No. This is nothing.

833
00:54:10,121 --> 00:54:11,039
Guys, it's nothing.

834
00:54:12,040 --> 00:54:14,125
<i>Tell Su-jeong to memorize it all.</i>

835
00:54:14,626 --> 00:54:16,919
<i>You didn't show the other kids, right?</i>

836
00:54:16,920 --> 00:54:20,589
<i>Please take care of my fundraiser
for the Superintendent of Education.</i>

837
00:54:20,590 --> 00:54:25,762
<i>Don't worry. We will donate enough
to have your funding overflowing.</i>

838
00:54:27,013 --> 00:54:30,350
If this exam goes well,
you'll be the Superintendent of Education.

839
00:54:31,476 --> 00:54:32,519
My gosh.

840
00:54:37,357 --> 00:54:39,400
Guys, it's really nothing!

841
00:54:39,401 --> 00:54:41,402
Mr. Cheon, is this real?

842
00:54:41,403 --> 00:54:42,695
Don't you trust me?

843
00:54:42,696 --> 00:54:45,030
- How could you?
- Everyone, sit down. Okay?

844
00:54:45,031 --> 00:54:46,324
I'll explain. No!

845
00:54:47,200 --> 00:54:49,159
- Da-yeon.
- We studied so damn hard!

846
00:54:49,160 --> 00:54:51,078
We have to go to SNU together, Da-yeon.

847
00:54:51,079 --> 00:54:52,956
Don't you trust me? Seriously?

848
00:54:56,293 --> 00:54:59,212
Will that give you enough energy to study?
Here, have more.

849
00:55:01,798 --> 00:55:02,882
You've turned out well.

850
00:55:04,134 --> 00:55:05,719
Just keep growing like that.

851
00:55:06,803 --> 00:55:09,346
Let me deal
with trash like Cheon Sang-yeol.

852
00:55:09,347 --> 00:55:11,016
I'll kick his butt.

853
00:55:13,768 --> 00:55:16,062
Thanks for the food. I'm off.

854
00:55:17,731 --> 00:55:19,482
Don't stay out too late.

855
00:55:23,361 --> 00:55:24,236
You believe that?

856
00:55:24,237 --> 00:55:26,238
- No, guys.
- Did you tell her?

857
00:55:26,239 --> 00:55:28,115
- I didn't.
- Did you really tell her?

858
00:55:28,116 --> 00:55:29,492
Guys, I really didn't!

859
00:55:30,327 --> 00:55:32,703
<i>I'm Hwang Gi-tae,
the Mirae Daehan Party leader.</i>

860
00:55:32,704 --> 00:55:35,581
As I mentioned
in the last press conference,

861
00:55:35,582 --> 00:55:39,835
the Educational Rights Protection Bureau
was created out of personal vendetta.

862
00:55:39,836 --> 00:55:42,212
But there is a bigger problem.

863
00:55:42,213 --> 00:55:44,673
They cannot be controlled,
no matter what they do,

864
00:55:44,674 --> 00:55:47,177
if they operate under the pretext
of ERPB activity,

865
00:55:48,053 --> 00:55:51,222
simply due to the extralegal Article 8
of the Establishment Act.

866
00:55:51,723 --> 00:55:55,976
"All acts by an inspector
during on-site guidance and investigations

867
00:55:55,977 --> 00:55:59,772
are not subject
to legal and institutional restrictions."

868
00:55:59,773 --> 00:56:04,069
Even if the inspector committed murder,
it would not be in violation of the law.

869
00:56:06,154 --> 00:56:08,739
Right now, you may be satisfied
with their actions.

870
00:56:08,740 --> 00:56:12,284
But in the future,
an irreparable tragedy is bound to occur.

871
00:56:12,285 --> 00:56:14,453
- Watch your mouth.
- Quiet down over there.

872
00:56:14,454 --> 00:56:16,748
- Stop talking nonsense.
- You know we're right!

873
00:56:17,832 --> 00:56:20,293
- Please be quiet.
- Minister of Education.

874
00:56:20,960 --> 00:56:23,129
Do you remember the trial two years ago?

875
00:56:24,672 --> 00:56:27,717
I have met someone
who clearly remembers that day.

876
00:56:29,427 --> 00:56:31,805
Is the prison guard,
Mr. Yoon Sun-yeol, present?

877
00:56:32,764 --> 00:56:34,349
- Yes, sir.
- Please come forward.

878
00:56:39,813 --> 00:56:43,108
Would you tell us what you witnessed
that day as it happened?

879
00:56:44,442 --> 00:56:49,030
As we escorted the accused, Cho Gyu-cheol,
to the transport vehicle after the trial,

880
00:56:49,531 --> 00:56:52,534
a man drove his car at him.

881
00:57:00,333 --> 00:57:03,586
Is this the man you are talking about?

882
00:57:04,629 --> 00:57:06,464
Yes, that's correct.

883
00:57:08,508 --> 00:57:10,342
Although it remained as an attempt,

884
00:57:10,343 --> 00:57:13,679
the inspector was so enraged
that he tried to commit murder.

885
00:57:13,680 --> 00:57:17,599
And the Minister of Education appointed
this person as the ERPB inspector.

886
00:57:17,600 --> 00:57:20,769
Do these people really have any right
to discuss education?

887
00:57:20,770 --> 00:57:23,440
The ERPB must be abolished at all costs.

888
00:57:25,150 --> 00:57:27,694
Mr. Yoon, you may return to your seat.

889
00:57:28,319 --> 00:57:31,156
Minister Choi,
you may make your counterarguments.

890
00:57:35,452 --> 00:57:36,703
Well...

891
00:57:37,203 --> 00:57:38,620
Before I proceed,

892
00:57:38,621 --> 00:57:41,624
I believe
there's a far more important issue

893
00:57:42,876 --> 00:57:45,335
that needs to be addressed first.

894
00:57:45,336 --> 00:57:49,090
Mr. Chairperson, please restrict
the discussion to relevant issues!

895
00:57:50,175 --> 00:57:51,216
Please restrict it!

896
00:57:51,217 --> 00:57:54,429
Please be quiet.
I will proceed as I see fit.

897
00:57:55,597 --> 00:57:59,850
Not long ago, the ERPB conducted
a full-scale investigation

898
00:57:59,851 --> 00:58:02,645
into Chukmyeong Foreign Language High.

899
00:58:03,855 --> 00:58:04,898
<i>As a result,</i>

900
00:58:05,607 --> 00:58:07,733
<i>we uncovered evidence of collusion</i>

901
00:58:07,734 --> 00:58:11,446
<i>among Cheon Sang-yeol, the parents,
and Noavis Institute</i>

902
00:58:12,030 --> 00:58:14,199
<i>to manipulate the grades.</i>

903
00:58:15,492 --> 00:58:18,452
<i>Cheon Sang-yeol
not only leaked exam questions</i>

904
00:58:18,453 --> 00:58:20,871
through Noavis Institute in advance,

905
00:58:20,872 --> 00:58:25,125
but he even leaked the exam papers
for the recent midterms.

906
00:58:25,126 --> 00:58:26,586
No way...

907
00:58:27,587 --> 00:58:29,130
Now I will disclose

908
00:58:30,256 --> 00:58:33,383
the names of parents involved
with Cheon Sang-yeol

909
00:58:33,384 --> 00:58:35,428
in the manipulation of grades.

910
00:58:40,266 --> 00:58:43,852
PH Group Chairman's wife, Kim Yeong-ran.

911
00:58:43,853 --> 00:58:44,979
Oh my God!

912
00:58:45,480 --> 00:58:47,731
<i>Daehan Media owner, Choi Pil-geun.</i>

913
00:58:47,732 --> 00:58:50,067
<i>Former NTS Commissioner, Joo Hyeon-ju.</i>

914
00:58:50,068 --> 00:58:53,321
<i>Former Chief Prosecutor
of Seoul Western District, Kim Jin-cheol.</i>

915
00:58:53,821 --> 00:58:56,156
<i>Doil Semiconductors CEO, Lee Jin-bong.</i>

916
00:58:56,157 --> 00:58:58,742
<i>Former Minister of Environment,
Kim Hui-jin.</i>

917
00:58:58,743 --> 00:59:01,453
<i>Researcher at Seo Bio, Ma Seong-hun.</i>

918
00:59:01,454 --> 00:59:03,539
<i>Dermatologist, Song Eun-yeong.</i>

919
00:59:03,540 --> 00:59:06,543
<i>Former MCST Vice Minister, Kim Jeong-ho.</i>

920
00:59:07,043 --> 00:59:09,211
<i>Ilseong Pharmaceuticals CEO, Ko Tae-hyeon.</i>

921
00:59:09,212 --> 00:59:11,505
Hyeonil Corporation CEO, Kim Sang-i.

922
00:59:11,506 --> 00:59:14,926
Bareun Bank Yeouido Branch Manager,
Kwon Min-ho.

923
00:59:17,428 --> 00:59:20,848
And lastly,
current member of the National Assembly,

924
00:59:21,432 --> 00:59:22,349
Lee Cheol-myeon.

925
00:59:22,350 --> 00:59:24,101
- Lee Cheol-myeon?
- Lee Cheol-myeon?

926
00:59:24,102 --> 00:59:25,353
- What?
- Really?

927
00:59:25,979 --> 00:59:28,105
- I think it's true.
- Hey, take photos.

928
00:59:28,106 --> 00:59:29,439
What are you trying to do?

929
00:59:29,440 --> 00:59:30,774
This is slander!

930
00:59:30,775 --> 00:59:32,693
- This is slander.
- It's slander!

931
00:59:32,694 --> 00:59:34,945
I'm going to sue you for defamation!

932
00:59:34,946 --> 00:59:36,030
Shut up!

933
00:59:36,656 --> 00:59:39,534
Or your damn child's face
will be all over the news.

934
00:59:45,123 --> 00:59:46,498
Are you not ashamed?

935
00:59:46,499 --> 00:59:49,626
Whenever your child's education
is discussed,

936
00:59:49,627 --> 00:59:51,795
why do you,
regardless of party or profession,

937
00:59:51,796 --> 00:59:53,923
cover your eyes, mouths, and ears,

938
00:59:55,341 --> 00:59:56,801
acting like fools?

939
00:59:57,594 --> 01:00:00,679
A teacher,
who should have been the fairest judge,

940
01:00:00,680 --> 01:00:03,474
pressured a student
from a difficult background

941
01:00:03,975 --> 01:00:07,562
and sabotaged their grades,
holding back their potential.

942
01:00:09,814 --> 01:00:11,316
<i>How can you call him a teacher?</i>

943
01:00:11,941 --> 01:00:15,153
<i>Not everyone who is called a teacher
is truly a teacher.</i>

944
01:00:16,946 --> 01:00:21,367
Did you say the ERPB is an organization
that only goes after children?

945
01:00:22,660 --> 01:00:26,789
Did you say we're now attacking teachers
only to avoid that allegation?

946
01:00:29,834 --> 01:00:31,002
You're wrong.

947
01:00:32,879 --> 01:00:37,216
The ERPB does not stand
with either the teachers or the students.

948
01:00:38,426 --> 01:00:40,053
We stand with the victims.

949
01:00:42,639 --> 01:00:45,223
<i>The ERPB exists
for those who have suffered</i>

950
01:00:45,224 --> 01:00:50,730
<i>when a student or a teacher
could not live up to their role.</i>

951
01:00:52,148 --> 01:00:54,359
If you call this a personal vendetta,
then it is.

952
01:00:54,859 --> 01:00:58,237
Someone needs to step up and take revenge
when the law fails.

953
01:00:58,738 --> 01:01:01,908
Only then can the victims
live their lives with peace of mind.

954
01:01:03,409 --> 01:01:06,286
<i>I will find every person
who got into college unfairly</i>

955
01:01:06,287 --> 01:01:09,540
<i>and the adults who were party to that.</i>

956
01:01:10,083 --> 01:01:11,292
<i>I will find them all</i>

957
01:01:12,001 --> 01:01:15,338
<i>and show them
what real fairness looks like.</i>

958
01:01:17,131 --> 01:01:22,512
I hope good teachers don't get called out
because of a few bad apples.

959
01:01:23,513 --> 01:01:24,347
Please

960
01:01:25,598 --> 01:01:27,516
act accordingly.

961
01:01:27,517 --> 01:01:29,435
Adults should act like adults

962
01:01:30,311 --> 01:01:32,105
and teachers like teachers.

963
01:01:44,867 --> 01:01:46,577
Jung Su-jeong, where are you?

964
01:01:47,078 --> 01:01:48,538
Hurry home already!

965
01:01:51,416 --> 01:01:53,667
<i>And I'm saying this just in case.</i>

966
01:01:53,668 --> 01:01:56,212
<i>Don't even think about
trying to leave the country.</i>

967
01:01:57,213 --> 01:01:59,298
<i>You're all under a travel ban.</i>

968
01:02:04,554 --> 01:02:08,056
Deputy Bong's equipment worked wonders.

969
01:02:08,057 --> 01:02:09,809
- It's a really expensive...
- Hey.

970
01:02:10,309 --> 01:02:12,937
- Should I carry that for you?
- No, I'm fine.

971
01:02:13,438 --> 01:02:15,106
- Teach him how to pack.
- Ma'am!

972
01:02:24,198 --> 01:02:25,408
Thank you.

973
01:02:36,794 --> 01:02:38,045
Thank you.

974
01:02:48,055 --> 01:02:49,807
Just do as you always have.

975
01:03:00,193 --> 01:03:01,485
- I recorded...
- So...

976
01:03:01,486 --> 01:03:04,697
What? Deputy Bong,
did you have something to say?

977
01:03:06,532 --> 01:03:07,658
No, it's nothing.

978
01:03:09,660 --> 01:03:11,913
Why are <i>you</i> crying, dude?

979
01:03:14,207 --> 01:03:16,082
You'd better head back and study.

980
01:03:16,083 --> 01:03:17,460
You've got this, right?

981
01:03:18,377 --> 01:03:19,337
Yes, sir.

982
01:03:25,968 --> 01:03:29,138
All you need to do now is study hard.
Good luck.

983
01:03:29,639 --> 01:03:33,184
Where did you get the list of the people
who manipulated the grades?

984
01:03:33,684 --> 01:03:36,812
I told each of them I'd let them off
if they gave me one name,

985
01:03:36,813 --> 01:03:37,979
and they all told me.

986
01:03:37,980 --> 01:03:38,898
Nice.

987
01:03:53,621 --> 01:03:56,915
All I did was buy him one cup of tea
during the consultation.

988
01:03:56,916 --> 01:03:59,584
We will speak when my attorney gets here!

989
01:03:59,585 --> 01:04:01,837
So what? I'm an assemblyman.
Don't touch me!

990
01:04:01,838 --> 01:04:03,296
Attorney Kang, where are you?

991
01:04:03,297 --> 01:04:05,716
- Why the hell aren't you here already?
- Please sit.

992
01:04:25,695 --> 01:04:29,198
I want to show you
how you ruined a child's life.

993
01:06:31,737 --> 01:06:34,699
Subtitle translation by: Lisa Kim
